 team to create positioning and messaging that differentiates our cross media and associated products work with the sales team and clients to understand market needs and how that influences the development of the product device sales strategies including pricing positioning and packaging of the various products qualifications  years of experience in the media planning andor research space including products methods market validation and sizing  or more years experience with the digital advertising research industry experience using comscore products preferred  or more years experience with product or project managing initiatives within an organization experience with video mobile social and market research in digital a plus familiarity with agile development framework a plus strong analytical orientationmust love data and be able to articulate the business impact ability to analyze large information sets in order to validate product quality required statistical knowledge is a plus excellent people and project management skills needed in order to interact with staff colleagues and crossfunctional teams and third parties excellent communication skills including both written and verbal to both technical and nontechnical audiences willing to travel upto  domestic and internationally sense of urgency responsive confident thorough not afraid to make decisions will to win and the intelligence to determine how to do so you know the competition as well as your own products resultsoriented team player who leads by example holds oneself accountable for performance takes ownership champions efforts with enthusiasm and conviction always learning and looked as the goto expert in the know constantly asking questions of our clients and ourselves about comscore comscore inc otc scor is a leading crossplatform measurement company that precisely measures audiences brands and consumer behavior everywhere  comscore completed its merger with rentrak corporation in january  to create the 